{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":399265,"duration_api_ms":365511,"num_turns":61,"result":"All amendments addressed. Here is the conforming JSON response:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Remediation round addressing 5 amendments from QA review: (1) Fixed four 'resume from failed run' tests by bumping transient_failure counts from 3→5 and adding start_paused=true. (2) Carried BinaryNotFound through the availability path by mapping AppError::BackendUnavailable to FailureClass::BinaryNotFound in error.rs, ensuring missing binaries fail immediately without retrying. (3) Made backoff sleep cancellable by wrapping tokio::time::sleep in tokio::select! against cancellation_token.cancelled(), with an immediate cancellation check after the select. (4) Added preserve_failed_artifacts method to PreparedCommand that moves Codex temp files to runtime/failed without requiring ChildOutput, and routed timeout errors through this preserving path instead of the destructive cleanup path.\",\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Fixed four resume-from-failed-run tests: bumped with_transient_failure counts from 3→5 (DocsUpdate, CiUpdate, Review, Implementation) and added #[tokio::test(start_paused = true)] to all four\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Changed AppError::BackendUnavailable failure_class mapping from TransportFailure to BinaryNotFound in src/shared/error.rs:302, making missing binary detection via check_availability non-retryable\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated agent_execution_test.rs test service_returns_backend_unavailable_as_transport_failure to assert BinaryNotFound instead of TransportFailure (renamed to service_returns_backend_unavailable_as_binary_not_found)\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Made backoff sleep cancellable in engine.rs:4637-4640 by wrapping tokio::time::sleep(backoff) in tokio::select! against cancellation_token.cancelled(), with an is_cancelled() check after the select to abort the retry when cancelled during backoff\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added PreparedCommand::preserve_failed_artifacts() method in process_backend.rs that moves Codex schema/message temp files to runtime/failed and writes a descriptive marker file, without requiring ChildOutput\",\n      \"order\": 5,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated both spawn_and_wait Err branches in invoke() to call preserve_failed_artifacts for timeout errors instead of the destructive cleanup(), preserving artifacts for operator inspection\",\n      \"order\": 6,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Verified all 677 tests pass, cargo clippy -D warnings clean, cargo fmt --check clean\",\n      \"order\": 7,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test: 677 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored\",\n    \"cargo clippy -- -D warnings: no warnings or errors\",\n    \"cargo fmt --check: no formatting differences\",\n    \"Four resume-from-failed tests now use transient_failure(stage, 5) matching TransportFailure max_attempts=5, with start_paused=true for instant backoff in CI\",\n    \"service_returns_backend_unavailable_as_binary_not_found test verifies BackendUnavailable maps to BinaryNotFound\",\n    \"Backoff cancellation: tokio::select! races sleep against cancellation_token.cancelled(), post-select is_cancelled() check prevents retry after cancellation\",\n    \"Timeout errors in invoke() now route through preserve_failed_artifacts instead of cleanup, keeping Codex temp files in runtime/failed for inspection\"\n  ],\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"The tokio test-util feature remains enabled unconditionally in Cargo.toml; this adds a small amount of compiled code to production builds but has no runtime impact\",\n    \"BackendUnavailable now maps universally to BinaryNotFound (non-retryable), which is correct for missing-binary and config-error cases but the variant name 'BinaryNotFound' is slightly misleading for pure configuration errors (e.g. missing API key). A more generic name like 'FatalInfrastructure' could be clearer but would require broader renaming\"\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2ab56341-dc03-426c-ace5-dda05f3b0827","total_cost_usd":3.8929747000000003,"usage":{"input_tokens":1200,"cache_creation_input_tokens":121778,"cache_read_input_tokens":5444383,"output_tokens":14647,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":121778,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":1200,"outputTokens":14647,"cacheReadInputTokens":5444383,"cacheCreationInputTokens":121778,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":3.855479,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":23,"outputTokens":1355,"cacheReadInputTokens":45377,"cacheCreationInputTokens":20928,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.0374957,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"99d59ef9-b6e0-40a5-8834-ce89ab84ec0b"}
